<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="574" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,1079]" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,765,791]" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">Etymology.</emphasis>
Refers to the word from the witoto 
<emphasis box="[745,848,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">ranoréde</emphasis>
which means small, and being a neutral genus, it is Latinized with the ending - 
<emphasis box="[454,496,802,827]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">ium</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,1079]" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,362,836,863]" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">Comparision.</emphasis>
The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jaiswara" authorityYear="2017" box="[703,808,838,863]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Perugryllus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="estiron">
<emphasis box="[703,808,838,863]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">P. estiron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following characteristics: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jaiswara" authorityYear="2017" box="[1183,1287,838,863]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Perugryllus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="estiron">
<emphasis box="[1183,1287,838,863]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">P. estiron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has four yellow spots on the pronotal disc, one at each end; tegmina covering the base of the third abdominal segment. Regarding genital structures, the median lobe notch V-shaped, pseudepiphallic ventral branch moderately sharp and curved inward, lateral lobe exceeding the length of the pseudepiphallic paramere. In contrast, 
<taxonomicName authority="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Orejuela, 2020" authorityName="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Orejuela" authorityYear="2020" box="[1143,1303,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Perugryllus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ranoredium" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1143,1303,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">P. ranoredium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1312,1377,945,971]" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1312,1377,945,971]" pageId="3" pageNumber="574" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
only has two spots located at the ends of the posterior margin of the pronotal disc; tegmina covering the first abdominal segment (
<figureCitation box="[258,346,1017,1043]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1963,1988]" captionTargetBox="[215,1369,218,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[201,1387,200,1938]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Perugryllus ranoredium n. sp. male. A. Habitus in lateral view and B. dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Head pronotum and wings in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3936760" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3936760/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Median lobe notch U-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[700,829,1017,1043]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1827,1852]" captionTargetBox="[169,1428,355,1786]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,344,1801]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Perugryllus ranoredium n. sp. male genitalia. A. Dorsal. B. Ventral and C. Lateral view respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3936762" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3936762/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">Figs. 2A, B</figureCitation>
); pseudepiphallic ventral branch notoriously sharp and curved inwards; lateral lobe without exceeding the length of the pseudepiphallic paramere (
<figureCitation box="[1175,1264,1053,1079]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1827,1852]" captionTargetBox="[169,1428,355,1786]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,344,1801]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Perugryllus ranoredium n. sp. male genitalia. A. Dorsal. B. Ventral and C. Lateral view respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3936762" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3936762/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
).
